    public interface Streamable
    Interface Streamable specifies the interface for an object that can be written to an output stream by class OutStream or read from an input stream by class InStream.

    A streamable object's class must have a no-argument constructor. When reading a streamable object from an InStream, an instance is created using the no-argument constructor, then the object's fields are read from the InStream using the readIn() method. However, the no-argument constructor need not be public. Also, the class itself need not be public. For further information, see the Instream.readObject() method.
